The government of Lagos State has announced a complete ban on the operations of commercial motorcycles in six local government areas in the state. Among the local governments are Ikeja, Surulere, Eti-Osa, Lagos Mainland, Lagos Island, and Apapa. Babajide Sanwo-Olu, governor of Lagos, announced the directive while briefing the state’s security agents on Wednesday. “The whole of Ikeja, Surulere, Eti-Osa, Lagos Mainland, Lagos Island, and Apapa local governments have been placed on a total ban effective from the first of June,” Sanwo-Olu said. “This is the first phase of banning that we are going to be embarking on, so that others should know. They should find something else to do.” 